---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout 
  title="Top Qualifying Conditions for Medical Marijuana in Florida" 
  description="Discover the top qualifying conditions for obtaining a medical marijuana card in Florida for 2026, including state regulations and guidelines."
>
  <!-- Hero Section -->
  <section class="bg-brand-mint py-16 lg:py-24 border-b border-brand-primary/10">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 text-center space-y-4">
      <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1 bg-brand-primary/10 text-brand-primary rounded-full text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-wider">
        📋 Medical Guidelines
      </span>
      <h1 class="text-4xl sm:text-5xl font-serif-headline text-brand-dark leading-tight uppercase">Top Qualifying Conditions for Medical Marijuana</h1>
      <p class="text-lg text-slate-600 max-w-2xl mx-auto leading-relaxed">
        Understand Florida's medical cannabis criteria for 2026. Review state requirements and learn if your diagnosis qualifies.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Content Section -->
  <section class="py-16 bg-white">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <div class="bg-white border border-brand-primary/10 rounded-3xl p-8 sm:p-12 shadow-whisper prose prose-slate max-w-none space-y-8">
        
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-serif-headline text-brand-dark">What conditions qualify for medical marijuana in Florida?</h2>
        <p class="text-slate-600 text-sm leading-relaxed">
          Under Florida Amendment 2 and current state laws, patients diagnosed with one of the following debilitating medical conditions are eligible for a medical marijuana registry card:
        </p>

        <ul class="list-disc pl-5 space-y-3 text-slate-600 text-sm">
          <li><strong>Cancer:</strong> Patients undergoing active treatment or managing chronic symptoms/pain from oncological conditions.</li>
          <li><strong>Epilepsy and Seizure Disorders:</strong> Refractory epilepsy or recurring seizures that do not respond to standard medical therapies.</li>
          <li><strong>Glaucoma:</strong> Severe ocular pressure or vision loss that has not responded to traditional drops or surgeries.</li>
          <li><strong>HIV/AIDS:</strong> Positive diagnosis of Human Immunodeficiency Virus or Acquired Immune Deficiency Syndrome.</li>
          <li><strong>Post-Traumatic Stress Disorder (PTSD):</strong> Diagnosed PTSD causing clinically significant distress or functional impairment.</li>
          <li><strong>Amyotrophic Lateral Sclerosis (ALS):</strong> Also known as Lou Gehrig's disease, a progressive neurodegenerative disease.</li>
          <li><strong>Crohn's Disease:</strong> Chronic inflammatory bowel disease causing debilitating digestive symptoms.</li>
          <li><strong>Parkinson's Disease:</strong> Chronic neurodegenerative movement disorder causing severe motor symptoms.</li>
          <li><strong>Multiple Sclerosis (MS):</strong> Chronic autoimmune disease affecting the central nervous system.</li>
          <li><strong>Medical Conditions of the Same Kind or Class:</strong> Chronic nonmalignant pain, severe anxiety, insomnia, or other conditions comparable to those listed above.</li>
          <li><strong>Terminal Illness:</strong> A condition diagnosed by a physician other than the certifying physician as terminal with a prognosis of under a year.</li>
          <li><strong>Chronic Nonmalignant Pain:</strong> Pain caused by a qualifying medical condition that persists beyond the usual course of that disease.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2 class="text-2xl font-serif-headline text-brand-dark">Understanding "Same Kind or Class" and Physician Discretion</h2>
        <p class="text-slate-600 text-sm leading-relaxed">
          The Florida Legislature included a clause allowing certifying doctors to recommend medical cannabis for symptoms and conditions of the <strong>"same kind or class"</strong> as the named conditions. This gives qualified physicians like Dr. Kelly Ennix King the clinical discretion to approve patients suffering from conditions such as:
        </p>

        <ul class="list-disc pl-5 space-y-2 text-slate-600 text-sm">
          <li>Severe and persistent muscle spasms</li>
          <li>Chronic anxiety and depression</li>
          <li>Severe insomnia or sleep disorders</li>
          <li>Rheumatoid arthritis and osteoarthritis</li>
          <li>Fibromyalgia and neuropathic pain</li>
          <li>Inflammatory bowel syndrome (IBS)</li>
        </ul>

        <div class="bg-brand-mint/40 p-6 rounded-2xl border border-brand-primary/10 my-8">
          <h3 class="text-base font-bold text-brand-dark mb-2">Clinical Evaluation Process</h3>
          <p class="text-slate-600 text-xs leading-relaxed">
            Even if you do not have a formal diagnosis of a listed condition, Dr. Kelly will evaluate your full medical history during your appointment. We help you obtain medical records if needed to confirm eligibility. Ready to get started? Check out our <a href="/evaluations" class="text-brand-accent font-bold hover:underline">Evaluations Guide</a>.
          </p>
        </div>

        <h2 class="text-2xl font-serif-headline text-brand-dark">How to Document Your Condition</h2>
        <p class="text-slate-600 text-sm leading-relaxed">
          To ensure a smooth evaluation at Releaf MD, we recommend patients bring proof of diagnosis or treatments. This can include doctor notes, diagnostic scans (X-rays, MRIs), list of prescriptions, or pathology reports. However, if you do not have these files, Dr. Kelly will conduct a full physical examination during your visit.
        </p>

        <div class="border-t border-slate-100 pt-8 flex flex-col sm:flex-row justify-between items-center gap-4">
          <p class="text-xs text-slate-500 italic">
            Read our <a href="/florida-medical-marijuana-card-guide" class="text-brand-primary font-bold hover:underline">Complete Florida Card Guide</a>.
          </p>
          <a target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" href="https://live.vcita.com/site/DrKellyKing/online-scheduling?service=xnfeicu6jent0179" class="bg-brand-accent hover:bg-brand-primary text-white font-bold px-6 py-3 rounded-full text-xs uppercase transition-colors shadow-md active-press">
            Schedule Assessment
          </a>
        </div>

      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
